# EnvironmentFile for iot-cellular-client.service.
#
# CELLULAR_CLIENT_ARGS is the literal argv tail for /usr/local/bin/cellular-client.
# The daemon owns the mangOH Yellow WP module: it drives the AT control tty
# (+ optional GNSS NMEA tty), connects the data context, and publishes modem
# status + GPS to the data-store under cell.* / gps.*. The lwm2m client mirrors
# gps.* into LwM2M Object 6 (Location); net-router routes the cellular slot
# (net.iface.cellular.name default "wwan0"). See /etc/iot/ds-schemas/cell.lua
# and apps/docs/tdd-mangoh-yellow-sensors.md §6.
#
# Most settings are hot via ds-cli (the daemon reads them at startup):
#   ds-cli set cell.apn '"internet"'           # operator/SIM APN
#   ds-cli set cell.modem.tty '"/dev/ttyUSB2"' # AT control device
#   ds-cli set cell.gps.tty '"/dev/ttyUSB1"'   # NMEA GNSS device (empty = off)
#   ds-cli set cell.poll.interval.sec '30'
#
# Bring-up: enumerate the WP interfaces first (`ls /dev/ttyUSB*`, `mmcli -L`),
# confirm which tty is the AT port vs NMEA vs DIAG. The AT/QMI/PPP data-path
# stack (ModemManager vs qmicli vs pure-AT) is selected per WP firmware — see
# the WAN open questions in the TDD doc.

CELLULAR_CLIENT_ARGS="--ds-sock=/run/iot/data_store.sock"
